reviews.review: The PERFECT end to a saga
Tried too hard make sense of the previous episode messes. A horrible way to conclude the Skywalker saga.

Waited 35 years to see how this ended, I haaaaated tlj it was a waste of a part 2, I feel this more then made up for it, only complaint and again I blame tlj bs is it was very fast paced to fix everything from part 2. Aside from that a fitting end.

Regarding the poor reviews: "It's true... all of it."
I can't in good conscience give this better than 2 1/2 stars. For a franchise that's existed for over 40 years to be so tone-deaf to a majority of it's fans (and not the crybabies who didn't like The Last Jedi) is unbelievable. No spoilers here, but my summary in a nutshell (which I acknowledge is as worthless as the next person's):
It didn't excite me or move me. It didn't intrigue me or challenge me. It didn't make me feel anything. The other reviews are spot-on in that it's too rushed. TROS doesn't spend time on character development because it assumes you're already all-in and just want to see flashy battles and hurry up to the ending.
Say what you want about The Last Jedi, but at least it was daring. The Rise of Skywalker was conventional, ho-hum, tent-pole IP moviemaking which plays to the lowest common denominator. I guess that's what happens when Disney gets involved.
Yet somehow Disney allowed Endgame to flourish, and they figured out how to put some emotional heft and consequences in their capstone. Endgame certainly wasn't perfect either, but they figured out in 10 years how to wrap things up better than Lucasfilm could in 42. 
The Rise of Skywalker is not the worst movie in the franchise (Phantom Menace will always have that honor). It IS the most disappointing though.
I think this movie is very satisfying, both to people who loved TLJ and people who hated it. An excellent conclusion to this trilogy.
great ending to the trilogy. fight scenes are great. best use of dueling and force use ive seen.
This movie make a mess is made not only on itself, but in the entre saga.
I am sad to say this; Star Wars is over this movie could have been so much better.

This is a movie that starts fast and doesn't stop until the end. It is everything you want from a Star Wars movie and more. It corrects and explains mistakes/things from the previous films while continuing on with the story. It is a satisfying end to the saga with plenty of fan service to go with it.
